COMPONENT NAME: LKM MSSQL to SQL (SOA XREF)
AUTHOR: Oracle
Description: - Loading Knowledge Module - Loads data from SQL SERVER to any ISO-92 database. - This module uses ODI Agent to read selected data from the database and write the result in the temporary table created dynamically.
Important restrictions for XREF usage: This LKM assumes that it is used in conjunction with the IKM SQL Control Append (SOA XREF)
Depending of the option SRC_UPDATE_DELETE_ACTION, this LKM could DELETE or UPDATE source records. Please check all options of this KM.
Update or Delete Action on Source

MANDATORY: Indicates what action to take on source records after integrating data into the target.
Valid values for this option are: - NONE: No action is taken on source records - UPDATE: Source records flag is updated according to SRC_UPD_COL and SRC_UPD_EXPRESSION - DELETE: Source records are deleted after integration

MANDATORY: Expressions that concatenates values from the PK to have them fit in a single large varchar column.
Example: for the source Orderline Table (aliased OLINE in the interface) you can use expression: TO_CHAR(OLINE.ORDER_ID) || '-' || TO_CHAR(OLINE.LINE_ID)

OPTIONAL: Indicate the source table's logical schema. The source table is the one from which we want to delete or update records after processing them. This logical schema is used to resolve the actual physical schema at runtime depending on the Context.
Example: ORDER_BOOKING
This option is required only when SRC_UPDATE_DELETE_ACTION is set to UPDATE or DELETE

OPTIONAL: Indicate the source table name of which we want to delete records after processing them.
Example: ORDERS
This option is required only when SRC_UPDATE_DELETE_ACTION is set to UPDATE or DELETE

OPTIONAL: Indicate the source table's alias within this interface. The source table is the one from which we want to delete or update records after processing them.
Example ORD
This option is required only when SRC_UPDATE_DELETE_ACTION is set to UPDATE or DELETE

OPTIONAL: Aliased source column name that holds the update flag indicator. The value of this column will be updated after integration when SRC_UPDATE_DELETE_ACTION is set to UPDATE with the expression literal SRC_UPD_EXPRESSION. The alias used for the column should match the one defined for the source table.
Example: ORD.LOADED_FLAG
This option is required only when SRC_UPDATE_DELETE_ACTION is set to UPDATE
Expression used for the UPD flag

OPTIONAL: Literal or expression used to update the SRC_UPD_COL. This value will be used to update this column after integration when SRC_UPDATE_DELETE_ACTION is set to UPDATE.
Example: 'RECORDS PROCESSED'
This option is required only when SRC_UPDATE_DELETE_ACTION is set to UPDATE
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.

<%if (!odiRef.getOption("SRC_UPDATE_DELETE_ACTION").equals("NONE")) { %> create table <%=odiRef.getObjectNameDefaultPSchema("PK__" + odiRef.getPop("I_POP"), "W")%> ( SKEY_VAL <%=odiRef.getDataType("SRC_VARCHAR", "1022", "")%> not null , constraint PK_<%=odiRef.getPop("I_POP")%> primary key (SKEY_VAL) ) <%}%>
Load Source PKs to PK Table

<%if (!odiRef.getOption("SRC_UPDATE_DELETE_ACTION").equals("NONE")) { %> insert into <%=odiRef.getObjectNameDefaultPSchema("PK__" + odiRef.getPop("I_POP"), "W")%> ( SKEY_VAL ) select <%=odiRef.getOption ("SRC_PK_EXPRESSION")%> from <%=odiRef.getFrom()%> where (1=1) <%=odiRef.getFilter()%> <%=odiRef.getJoin()%> <%=odiRef.getJrnFilter()%> <%=odiRef.getGrpBy()%> <%=odiRef.getHaving()%> <%}%>

select <%=odiRef.getPop("DISTINCT_ROWS")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[EXPRESSION]\t[ALIAS_SEP] [CX_COL_NAME]", ",\n\t", "", "")%>, <%=odiRef.getOption("SRC_PK_EXPRESSION")%> SKEY_VAL from <%=odiRef.getFrom()%> <%if (!odiRef.getOption("SRC_UPDATE_DELETE_ACTION").equals("NONE")) { %> , <%=odiRef.getObjectNameDefaultPSchema("PK__" + odiRef.getPop("I_POP"), "W")%> P__K <%}%> where (1=1) <%=odiRef.getFilter()%> <%if (!odiRef.getOption("SRC_UPDATE_DELETE_ACTION").equals("NONE")) { %> and <%=odiRef.getOption("SRC_PK_EXPRESSION")%> = P__K.SKEY_VAL <%}%> <%=odiRef.getJoin()%> <%=odiRef.getJrnFilter()%> <%=odiRef.getGrpBy()%> <%=odiRef.getHaving()%>

<% if ("C".equals(odiRef.getJrnInfo( "JRN_METHOD"))) { %> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> delete from <%=odiRef.getTable( "L" , "JRN_NAME" , "A" )%> where JRN_CONSUMED = '1' <%=odiRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>

<% if ("C".equals(odiRef.getJrnInfo( "JRN_METHOD"))) { %> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> update <%=odiRef.getTable( "L" , "JRN_NAME" , "A" )%> set JRN_CONSUMED = '1' where (1=1) <%=odipRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>
Update or Delete from source table

<%if (odiRef.getOption("SRC_UPDATE_DELETE_ACTION").equals("DELETE")) { %> delete <%=odiRef.getOption("SRC_PK_TABLE_ALIAS")%> from <%=odiRef.getObjectName("L", odiRef.getOption("SRC_PK_TABLE_NAME"), odiRef.getOption("SRC_PK_LOGICAL_SCHEMA"), "D")%> <%=odiRef.getOption("SRC_PK_TABLE_ALIAS")%> where <%=odiRef.getOption("SRC_PK_EXPRESSION")%> in ( select SKEY_VAL from <%=odiRef.getObjectNameDefaultPSchema("PK__" + odiRef.getPop("I_POP"), "W")%> ) <%}%> <%if (odiRef.getOption("SRC_UPDATE_DELETE_ACTION").equals("UPDATE")) { %> update <%=odiRef.getOption("SRC_PK_TABLE_ALIAS")%> set <%=odiRef.getOption("SRC_UPD_COL")%> = <%=odiRef.getOption("SRC_UPD_EXPRESSION")%> from <%=odiRef.getObjectName("L", odiRef.getOption("SRC_PK_TABLE_NAME"), odiRef.getOption("SRC_PK_LOGICAL_SCHEMA"), "D")%> <%=odiRef.getOption("SRC_PK_TABLE_ALIAS")%>, <%=odiRef.getObjectNameDefaultPSchema("PK__" + odiRef.getPop("I_POP"), "W")%> where <%=odiRef.getOption("SRC_PK_EXPRESSION")%> = SKEY_VAL <%}%>
